# Project Guidelines

## Rules
- Use TypeScript for all new files.
- Favor functional components over classes.
- Place all components in `/src/components`.
- Check existing utility functions before creating new ones.
- Make components reusable where required.
- Any Delete buttons should always require user confirmation. 
- Refer to backend swagger API documentation: http://localhost:3001/api-docs/
- Create appropriate unit tests for code, for existing code that does not have unit tests and on all newly generated code. 
- Structure the code for maintainability
- Ensure all processes that are started during executing a prompt are properly terminated.
- Anywhere currency field is used default to INR (Indian Rupee)
- When display currency information, ensure correct currency symbol is used
- When adding table action buttons such as Edit, Delete or add, always use icon buttons. All action buttons should be the first column and delete button should be the last column.
- All delete confirmations should display modal confirmation dialog with one piece of information for user to type as confirmation.

